The paper deals with the analysis of the clustering phase transition in random XORSAT instances, which is a fundamental problem in computational complexity theory. This makes cs.CC (Computational Complexity) the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the study of the structure of hypergraphs associated with XORSAT instances, which is a topic in discrete mathematics, making cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) another likely sub-category. The paper also uses tools from information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.AI), and statistical learning (cs.LG) to analyze the clustering phase transition and construct sparse bases for the set of solutions.
